UST SLAMS CORRUPTION IN FLOOD CONTROL PROJECTS

The University of Santo Tomas on Wednesday, Sept. 17, strongly condemned alleged corruption behind flood control projects, saying funds meant to save lives were misused for personal gain.

Calling it a “betrayal of public trust” and “a deep injustice to the poor,” UST urged swift and independent investigations, stressing that “in the face of corruption, silence is complicity; partiality is injustice.”

The university also called on Thomasians and Filipinos to demand honesty, accountability, and integrity from public officials.

'CORRUPTION IS NOT ONLY THEFT OF MONEY-IT IS THEFT OF OUR FUTURE'

Faculty members of the Philippine Normal University (PNU) have released a position paper condemning systemic corruption in government and pressing for accountability in light of the recently exposed flood control scandal.

The PNU Faculty Union said corruption has robbed generations of dignity and opportunity, stressing that justice must reach not only low-level implementers but also high-ranking officials and contractors allegedly involved in irregularities.

 Philippine Normal University Manila Faculty Union
